data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[t∫au]
*danh từ
 ■giống chó su (Trung quốc)
 ■(từ lóng) thức ăn
◘[chow]
saying && slang
 ■food, something to eat
 ⁃I'm starved. Let's get some chow.

Anh - Anh
chow
[tʃaʊ]
■ noun
1》 informal food.
2》 (also chow chow) a dog of a sturdy Chinese breed with a tail curled over its back, a bluish-black tongue, and typically a dense thick coat.
■ verb (chow down) N. Amer. informal eat.
Origin
C19: shortened from chow chow.
